rivals as the Thai financial sector is liberalised and opened more to
foreign banks.
Siam City Bank reported a 68 per cent rise in its net profit to Bt1.98bn in
1993 from Bt1.17bn the previous year. The two banks have yet to divulge
further details of their results.
