<HEADLINE>
FT  04 FEB 94 / Kleinwort launch is UK record
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The public offer for Kleinwort Benson's European Privatisation Investment
Trust was more than Pounds 380m oversubscribed, confirming its position as
the largest UK investment trust launch ever.
Applications for Pounds 560m-worth of shares were received during the public
offer, which closed on Wednesday, giving the fund a potential size of Pounds
880m, as Pounds 320m had already been raised through an institutional
placing, but it was capped at Pounds 500m.
However, the Mercury European Privatisation Trust has set its maximum size
at Pounds 575m, so it could soon beat Kleinwort's record. The Mercury fund
raised Pounds 325m in its placing, which closed on Wednesday, and is seeking
a further Pounds 100m from an intermediaries offer, closing February 25, and
Pounds 150m from a public offer, closing March 2.
Applications for shares in the Kleinwort trust are being scaled back by
about two-thirds. Mr Simon White, managing director of Kleinwort Benson
Investment Trusts, said the company believed that Pounds 500m was an
appropriate size given the state of development and liquidity of the target
investment area.
If all the disappointed investors from the Kleinwort offer now apply for the
Mercury fund, it will also be oversubscribed.
Investors who applied for the minimum 2,000 Kleinwort shares will receive
700. Applications for up to 2m shares will be allocated approximately 31.45
per cent, and those for more than 2m shares will receive 31.45 of the first
2m and 25 per cent thereafter.
One free warrant will be issued with every five shares.
</TEXT>
