FT  04 FEB 94 / French shipyard confirms Swan bid
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Constructions Mecaniques de Normandie, the French shipbuilder, last night
confirmed it intends to make an offer to buy Swan Hunter, the Tyneside
shipyard which has been in receivership since May, Chris Tighe writes.
The French company recently beat Swan Hunter in the fight for a Pounds 50m
Oman patrol boats order. Mr Fred Henderson, chairman of English subsidiary
CMN Support Services, said: 'We intend to make an offer subject to the
preconditions being sorted out.' He added: 'We would hope to largely
continue the present workforce.' He could not give any indication of the
value of the bid.
Mr Henderson said good progress had been made in two days of talks in
identifying and clearing the many outstanding matters which needed to be
resolved, including legal points on the transfer of undertakings. A
programme had been agreed to address these issues. He hoped an offer would
be made before the end of March.
