<HEADLINE>
FT  04 FEB 94 / Malta urges early talks on EU entry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LIONEL BARBER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Malta yesterday called for an 'immediate' start of accession negotiations to
join the European Union, arguing that it would shortly overcome the final
economic obstacles to entry, Lionel Barber reports from Brussels. Dr Eddie
Fenech Adami, the Maltese prime minister, said in Brussels that his
government would 'in a matter of weeks' meet the European Commission's
requirements for regulatory reforms in financial services, competition and
consumer protection.
The Maltese declaration puts the European Commission and the 12 EU member
states on the spot. Though sympathetic towards Malta's application,
sentiment has leaned toward a delay until the end of enlargement
negotiations with Finland, Austria, Sweden and Norway. But Dr Fenech Adami
said Malta intended to ensure the Commission stuck to the conditions set
down on its generally favourable opinion on EU membership issued last year.
</TEXT>
