<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
McGraw-Hill, the US publisher and broadcaster, expects to show financial
progress in 1994 after flat fourth-quarter earnings, and a loss for 1993 due
to an acquisition charge, Reuter reports from New York.
It said it took a non-recurring charge of Dollars 160.8m, or Dollars 3.27 a
share, for a 50 per cent interest in MacMillan/McGraw-Hill School
Publishing.
As a result, 1993 earnings were Dollars 11.4m, or 23 cents, against Dollars
28.6m, or 58 cents.
For the fourth quarter ended December 31, the company reported earnings of
Dollars 44.9m, or 91 cents, compared with Dollars 44.7m, or 91 cents, in the
fourth quarter of 1992.
