<TEXT>
Plasmon, a privately-owned manufacturer of optical memory disks and disk
systems, has paid an undisclosed amount to acquire International Data
Engineering, a US company which makes the robotics at the heart of optical
disk storage systems.
Plasmon makes about 10,000 optical disks a month; its optical storage
systems, or jukeboxes, cost between Pounds 9,000 and Pounds 200,000.
Turnover was Pounds 13.5m last year, with profits of Pounds 292,000.
IDE is based in Minneapolis, Minnesota, where it makes jukebox mechanisms
and tape autoloaders.
