FT  03 FEB 94 / People: Royal Insurance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Robert Mendelsohn, 47, is to take over as chief executive officer of the US
subsidiary of ROYAL INSURANCE, following the retirement of William Buckley,
57, from his positions both as president and chief executive officer of the
company and as a director of Royal's holding company.
Until last year, Mendelsohn was president and chief operating officer of WR
Berkley Corporation, a successful non-life company whose recent operating
results have compared favourably with the rest of the US industry. If
Berkley's advertising slogan - 'Volume is vanity, profit is sanity' - is any
indication, Mendelsohn should feel at home with Royal's emphasis on
underwriting discipline rather than market share.
Royal's US company, which is based in Charlotte, North Carolina, is ranked
in the top 30 property and casualty insurance companies in the United States
and is rated A- by AM Best Company. It has a share of just under 1 per cent
of the US market.
