FT  03 FEB 94 / New school check
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr John Patten, education secretary, yesterday took extra powers to
intervene in the running of schools in England and Wales. Inspectors will
now be asked to visit schools which have not been classified as 'failing' by
