<HEADLINE>
FT  03 FEB 94 / Health chief quits in Brazil trip row
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND ADBURGHAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The director of Health Promotion Wales, a government-funded body, resigned
last night after Labour alleged he had claimed fraudulent expenses for
foreign travel, Roland Adburgham writes.
Professor John Catford was accused under parliamentary privilege by Mr
Rhodri Morgan, MP for Cardiff West and a Labour frontbench spokesman on
Wales, of taking a trip to Brazil for personal reasons. Mr Morgan said: 'It
is yet another unacceptable face of Welsh quangoland.'
The professor, who had been executive director of the body since 1987, also
resigned from the chair of health promotion and education at the University
of Wales. Last night, he said his resignations were because a 'silly and
regrettable' affair with a female colleague while on a professional trip to
Brazil, had become public knowledge. 'There was no abuse of public funds,'
he said.
</TEXT>
